76561198256879294,Recommended,280720,28361592,"Posted: 14 December, 2016",all,TheAnonymous1,"Imagine Earth is a sort of simplified city building game with an easily understood user interface and light hearted characters to meet with somewhat cartoonish nature. You are a colony manager and you build cities in sandbox or campaign with the limit of how much punishment the planet can take before eco collapse. It is a fun game to play if you have a little free time, but I will say that it gets somewhat boring after 20 hours or so. The game is almost to simple sometimes because once you build your city to a good size, then it is smooth sailing until you either stop expanding or destroy your colony with a environment collapse (unless you are in the campaign then you finish the mission). One thing I really found annoying was the tech tree because you earn tech points over time building cities to invest in the tree. You can also buy tech from traders, but once a decision is made, you have to live with it for every new game you start. You cannot start the tech tree over, but buy techs that counter it and this applies to every sandbox and campaign mission started. I will rate the game recommended because it in early access and still is updating regularly. It was fun for a short time, but I would have gotten it on sale If I had the opportunity to start over."
