,Recommended,280720,34473574,Posted: 24 August,all,Machismo01,"This has shaped up to be a really good game. It is satisfying with the layers of content and systems. Consider an ecological Civ-ish game where the focus is mainly on building large or lots of cities and strong economy. Make money, but don't drive the environment into collapse.Each mission supports some degree of progression from the last (mainly the tech tree unlock).Planet building has a number of puzzle-like elements requiring some thought and planning unique to the resources and layout of the planet. For example, a wood good structure produces quite a bit more wood if next to forests. Cities require adjacent urban centers to level up. These types of system add constant limits to what you can do, but there seems to be always a way around it. It results in a really fun gameplay loop that is always teaching you."
,Recommended,280720,35078227,Posted: 19 September,all,Stryderunknown,"This is a mix of City builder and Strategy game since the triangular tiles that each building type occupies can only be bordered by three other tiles that have either negative or positive influences.  It has similarities to Anno in having requirements to upgrade tiles (like needing more than one food type or good) The hours I've spent so far have been attempting to be a completionist with the missions since each campaign mission has a number of objectives to complete.Some  of the objectives  are completed by just following the narrative, The one that is a little awkward is the objective that requires you to treasure hunt a particular special resource, as finding it can be simple, getting it in your zone of control however is a different story.There is an online leaderboard for players to compare scores in how well they did, currently the scores look like people have actually be playing it rather than just manipulating it and getting to the top of the board.  I don't know how long that will last though.Currently it appears the game actually has a pretty small footprint in regards to download size (currently less than 1Gb) so for those of you that don't want to spend hours downloading larger games, this might well be one for you.  (check the Demo to get an idea of what it's like)"
